    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-06-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-06-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="260"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d260">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/2032</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Irkutsk</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_HEL1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harris</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="2" xml:id="d260fn2">Sent via the Consulate at Vladivostok.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Irkutsk</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-06-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 10, 1918</hi>
                        </date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received June 15, 640
                        p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>17. On June 2 Social Committee’s [<hi rend="italic">sic</hi>] Party captured
                    Nizhne-udinsk from Bolsheviks and sent ultimatum to Soviet here ordering <pb
                        facs="0291" n="201" xml:id="pg_201"/> surrender Irkutsk within twenty-four
                    hours. Local Soviet did not reply but sent Red Army west of city to meet
                    attacking force. Latter has not yet come. No news obtainable as all
                    communications west of city interrupted.</p>
                <closer>[<signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HEL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Harris</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>]</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
